“With the support of the UK government, philanthropists, governments elsewhere and citizens like you, we can make the social problem of malnutrition a minor fact of history,” said Tracy Ullman, a spokeswoman for The Power of Nutrition, speaking to the public at a live concert in London in April 2018.
The organization also said that after 5,000 “acts” calling for better nutrition for mothers and children, the UK government announced funding for the Power of Nutrition project, aimed at improving the nutrition of 5 million mothers and children.
In response to one of the common questions on his website, "Why do you think you can overcome extreme poverty?",
Global Citizen said: “It’s a long and difficult journey, so sometimes we’ll fail and fail.
“However, like the civil rights and anti-apartheid movements before us, we will succeed because together we are stronger.”
Janet Jackson, The Weeknd, Sean Mendes, Cardi B, and Jianell Mona are just a few of the star performers who will perform at the New York City festival this year, with Deborah-Lee Farness and Hugh Jackman leading the show.
