The defendant, Khalid Barnes, was convicted of the murder of two drug dealers and eventually sentenced to life imprisonment in September 2009.
The last federal execution was in New York City in 1953, when Julius and Ethel Rosenberg were executed after being convicted of conspiracy to spy on the Soviet Union during the Cold War two years earlier.
